Show HN: MoonPier for NFT, presale before launch
text:
Hi Hackers!

I'm Justin, and though it may not be the best time to showcase my web3 project, I would like to share MoonPier with you! MoonPier enables creators to pre-sell NFTs using ETH, instead of simply collecting a whitelist before an NFT launch.

Over the past three months, my friends and I have created multiple NFT collections with less-than-stellar sales results. We wondered if there could be a Kickstarter-like platform, it would save us on deployment fees before achieving "collection market fit".

MoonPier is now live on the Sepolia testnet! I'd be grateful for any feedback or suggestions you may have. If you're interested in giving it a try, please let me know your thoughts. Your insights are invaluable to us!

Ask HN: What percentage of time are you wearing headphones/earbuds?
text:
Ever since noise-cancelling headphones became popular and affordable, I've noticed myself becoming pretty incessantly attached to them. Probably 75% of my awake time I am wearing them and/or listening to something, and while I don't think this is terribly abnormal, I'm almost certain it's been terrible for my mental capacity.

Beyond that I have running theory that noise cancelling contributes to my depression by further enforcing a sort of isolation.

Curious if anyone else has felt the same effects.
